  <datafield tag="245" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">SCALP, a platform dedicated to material modifications and characterization under ion beam.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="260" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="c">2017-03-11</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">SCALP (Synthesis and Characterization using ion AcceLerators for Pluridisciplinary research) is a platform dedicated to characterization and modification of materials using ion beams. Located at CSNSM, a joint research unit of CNRS and Université Paris-Sud, Orsay-France, it is composed, on the one hand, by a 2 MV Tandem/Van de Graaff accelerator and a 190 kV implanter, both possibly coupled with a Transmission Electron Microscope. On the other hand, a 40 kV separator is dedicated to magnetic isotopic separation and enables either a pure isotope beam to be delivered, or mono-isotopic targets (purity of the order of ppm) to be manufactured by implantation or by deposition.</subfield>
